      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">wallace87 wrote:</div><div class="orig">I downloaded AVG and yes i have a virus or 2.</div></div> <br /> <br />Hi there, my advice right now. Get rid of AVG and install Avira. It's a free anti-virus as well, but loads better than AVG. Most of my customers who have virus infections have AVG on their systems. <br />Another program I suggest you to get would be Malwarebytes Anti-Malware. It's a free malware scanner that will work together with Avira. <br /> <br />I have 2 women in my household that don't have a clue when it comes to computers and they both used to get viruses fairly easily. I installed both Avira and Malwarebytes and told them to run a scan weekly. They haven't had a virus since. <br /> <br />I hope you get everything sorted out! <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 19th 2010  4:42pm by Shurbryn </span></i></div>
